1
00:00:05,531 --> 00:00:07,131
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,191 --> 00:00:08,761
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:09,231 --> 00:00:10,861
All right, that's a wrap, everyone.
Good work.

4
00:00:11,161 --> 00:00:12,931
- Good work.
- Yes, good job, everyone.

5
00:00:13,001 --> 00:00:14,871
- Great job.
- Yes, you too.

6
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:16,201
- Councilor Hwang.
- Great work.

7
00:00:17,471 --> 00:00:19,341
- Is everyone here?
- Yes.

8
00:00:19,541 --> 00:00:22,411
I was impressed by your remarks,
Dr. Han.

9
00:00:23,411 --> 00:00:28,011
I was just speaking my mind.
Thank you for listening carefully.

10
00:00:28,311 --> 00:00:30,251
Well, they were worth listening to.

11
00:00:30,251 --> 00:00:32,751
I'll be sure
to review your suggestions.

12
00:00:33,051 --> 00:00:37,691
Thank you, Councilor Hwang,
for your interest in Onjeong Market.

13
00:00:39,761 --> 00:00:40,991
Well, today...

14
00:00:42,331 --> 00:00:43,731
Thank you for your hard work,
Councilor Hwang.

15
00:00:45,231 --> 00:00:46,531
But you know, Dr. Yang...

16
00:00:47,071 --> 00:00:48,771
You were unusually quiet today.

17
00:00:50,301 --> 00:00:52,941
Is it because you got greedy
for screen time and got edited out?

18
00:00:53,341 --> 00:00:54,371
So, you decided to self-edit?

19
00:00:54,571 --> 00:00:55,611
Pardon?

20
00:00:55,611 --> 00:00:59,351
Luckily, thanks to Dr. Han,
you won't be edited out this time.

21
00:01:00,651 --> 00:01:01,921
Well, I'll see you all next time.

22
00:01:02,981 --> 00:01:05,691
- Great work, everyone.
- Yes, take care, Councilor Hwang.

23
00:01:06,251 --> 00:01:08,021
- See you next time.
- Yes.

24
00:01:08,091 --> 00:01:10,691
- Yes, take care.
- Right, let's go.

25
00:01:11,931 --> 00:01:12,931
Well...

26
00:01:19,331 --> 00:01:21,601
He intentionally let Seong Mi
do all the talking...

27
00:01:22,401 --> 00:01:24,571
and deliberately cut everything
I had to say.

28
00:01:25,911 --> 00:01:29,381
Don't be too disappointed, honey.
From now on, let's...

29
00:01:29,441 --> 00:01:31,141
not rely so much on being on TV.

30
00:01:31,141 --> 00:01:33,481
We'll show Councilor Hwang
real results,

31
00:01:33,551 --> 00:01:35,281
and he'll have to recognize
your talent.

32
00:01:38,551 --> 00:01:40,051
Gosh, it's finally over.

33
00:01:40,721 --> 00:01:43,921
- Tell me about it.
- Honey, are you okay?

34
00:01:43,921 --> 00:01:45,631
You seem tired today.

35
00:01:45,761 --> 00:01:49,401
I'm fine.
It's nice to be out for a change.

36
00:01:49,561 --> 00:01:52,801
Yes. Hey, let's wait for Woo Jae
and go home together.

37
00:01:53,031 --> 00:01:56,041
But Dae Han was here earlier.
Did he leave already?

38
00:01:56,271 --> 00:01:59,641
He came to watch but probably bolted
when it dragged on. That guy...

39
00:01:59,711 --> 00:02:01,041
Goodness.

40
00:02:01,641 --> 00:02:02,911
This baby...

41
00:02:03,441 --> 00:02:05,141
is yours, honey.

42
00:02:08,051 --> 00:02:12,491
What? What kind of ridiculous thing
are you saying right now?

43
00:02:12,621 --> 00:02:13,621
Oh, for goodness' sake.

44
00:02:14,551 --> 00:02:17,461
I'm telling you,
I'm pregnant with your baby.

45
00:02:18,391 --> 00:02:20,031
But you were on the pill.

46
00:02:20,691 --> 00:02:24,331
Honey, the pill isn't
100 percent effective, you know.

47
00:02:24,631 --> 00:02:25,631
Right.

48
00:02:26,931 --> 00:02:29,271
Here, look. It's so cute.

49
00:02:32,771 --> 00:02:37,081
It's small, so it's hard to see,
but its profile looks like you.

50
00:02:38,341 --> 00:02:41,851
Fine, let's say you're pregnant.
But how do you know it's mine?

51
00:02:42,281 --> 00:02:45,081
You were seeing that jerk
while we were living together.

52
00:02:45,151 --> 00:02:48,961
Him? I told him I didn't want kids,
so...

53
00:02:49,021 --> 00:02:50,961
he got a vasectomy a long time ago.

54
00:02:51,361 --> 00:02:53,591
Now, that's 100 percent effective
birth control.

55
00:02:53,991 --> 00:02:56,761
Besides, if you count back the days,
it's definitely your baby, honey.

56
00:02:58,501 --> 00:03:01,501
- So what do you want from me?
- What do you think?

57
00:03:04,001 --> 00:03:05,341
We have to get back together.

58
00:03:06,111 --> 00:03:07,171
What?

59
00:03:08,341 --> 00:03:11,711
Just accept it.
We signed the papers,

60
00:03:11,781 --> 00:03:16,221
but if a baby came to us now,
fate must be bringing us together.

61
00:03:18,281 --> 00:03:19,291
You're not coming in.

62
00:03:20,151 --> 00:03:22,161
Don't you dare set foot in my house.
Got it?

63
00:03:22,591 --> 00:03:24,661
- Honey.
- Don't call me that!

64
00:03:26,931 --> 00:03:28,031
Don't call me that.

65
00:03:29,861 --> 00:03:31,231
I'm not your "honey."

66
00:03:32,671 --> 00:03:34,171
I'm in love with someone else.

67
00:03:34,931 --> 00:03:36,201
So don't call me that.

68
00:03:36,671 --> 00:03:37,971
What? Who is it?

69
00:03:39,111 --> 00:03:42,341
Don't tell me it's Ji Hu's mom.
You're just trying to get to me.

70
00:03:42,411 --> 00:03:43,741
You were just kidding, right?

71
00:03:43,811 --> 00:03:45,911
I don't joke about things like that.
Understand?

72
00:03:47,451 --> 00:03:48,451
Go home.

73
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:51,991
I'll call you
after I've had some time to think.

74
00:03:52,551 --> 00:03:53,551
Now, go home.

75
00:03:54,051 --> 00:03:55,051
Wait, I...

76
00:03:55,791 --> 00:03:57,421
Fine. Okay, then...

77
00:03:59,161 --> 00:04:02,201
I'll be nearby,
so please call me soon.

78
00:04:10,741 --> 00:04:12,541
This morning sickness is awful.

79
00:04:14,941 --> 00:04:16,281
It must be a boy.

80
00:04:26,351 --> 00:04:29,121
- You shouldn't get cold. Here.
- I'm okay.

81
00:04:29,191 --> 00:04:33,261
- No. Wear this. Here.
- Hey, the cameras stopped rolling.

82
00:04:33,791 --> 00:04:35,191
You can drop the act now.

83
00:04:35,631 --> 00:04:38,161
What? As if you two don't always act
like complete strangers.

84
00:04:38,231 --> 00:04:42,141
- You think I'm blind? It's an act.
- What?

85
00:04:42,201 --> 00:04:46,011
Look, I get that you're upset
things didn't go your way,

86
00:04:46,141 --> 00:04:48,211
but don't take it out on us,
all right?

87
00:04:48,341 --> 00:04:51,841
Hey, I practically begged you,
and you let your wife...

88
00:04:51,911 --> 00:04:53,281
hog all the screen time.
Are you happy?

89
00:04:53,351 --> 00:04:56,981
Is it our fault you couldn't speak
because you were unprepared?

90
00:04:57,151 --> 00:05:00,091
Blaming others
for your own incompetence...

91
00:05:00,251 --> 00:05:02,361
That's a textbook case
of shifting the blame.

92
00:05:02,861 --> 00:05:05,461
You're quite greedy, Doctor.

93
00:05:05,731 --> 00:05:09,331
You get plenty of TV gigs,
and so does Dr. Gong.

94
00:05:09,461 --> 00:05:13,331
- Did you need to hog this show too?
- Excuse me.

95
00:05:13,601 --> 00:05:16,601
Have we ever once asked
to be on this show?

96
00:05:16,841 --> 00:05:20,541
You're the one who begged us to join
using every trick in the book.

97
00:05:20,611 --> 00:05:23,781
Come on, honey. Let's just go, okay?
Don't waste your breath. Let's go.

98
00:05:23,841 --> 00:05:25,711
- That's right. Mom, let's just go.
- Yes, let's go.

99
00:05:25,781 --> 00:05:27,211
- Good grief.
- That jerk... Darn it.

100
00:05:27,281 --> 00:05:29,321
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

101
00:05:29,621 --> 00:05:31,821
Why did you have to go
and pick a fight?

102
00:05:31,851 --> 00:05:34,151
Hey, I didn't start anything...

103
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:36,591
But why are you taking their side?

104
00:05:36,961 --> 00:05:39,861
I'm not taking anyone's side.
We still have more shooting to do.

105
00:05:39,931 --> 00:05:41,661
I'm just saying we should try
to finish on good terms.

106
00:05:45,131 --> 00:05:46,231
What is with her?

107
00:06:01,381 --> 00:06:02,381
What?

108
00:06:02,981 --> 00:06:04,281
Your dad is going where?

109
00:06:04,521 --> 00:06:07,451
Saudi Arabia. He said
he's really going there for work.

110
00:06:08,151 --> 00:06:10,861
He asked me to tell you
he'll send child support regularly.

111
00:06:11,961 --> 00:06:13,061
Oh, really?

112
00:06:14,131 --> 00:06:15,431
But he said he's going alone.

113
00:06:16,501 --> 00:06:17,501
Why?

114
00:06:17,761 --> 00:06:19,271
He said he broke up with that woman.

115
00:06:20,301 --> 00:06:21,301
What?

116
00:06:21,371 --> 00:06:25,471
She won't get in the way
of you and Mr. Gong, right?

117
00:06:29,681 --> 00:06:32,851
By the way,
why were you so quiet today?

118
00:06:33,251 --> 00:06:35,651
You prepared so much
to talk to Councilor Hwang.

119
00:06:36,151 --> 00:06:38,251
Well, I don't know.

120
00:06:48,091 --> 00:06:50,501
- Honey.
- What? Yes.

121
00:06:51,701 --> 00:06:55,001
You stepped out before the shoot
to talk on the phone. Who was it?

122
00:06:55,201 --> 00:06:56,241
What?

123
00:06:56,671 --> 00:06:59,571
Oh, that was Eun Bin.
She said a customer at the store...

124
00:06:59,641 --> 00:07:01,211
had a question.

125
00:07:01,441 --> 00:07:02,781
I see.

126
00:07:03,811 --> 00:07:06,181
All right,
I'm going to go get some water,

127
00:07:06,611 --> 00:07:08,921
- so you go ahead and wash up first.
- Okay, sure.

128
00:07:09,021 --> 00:07:10,121
All right.

129
00:07:22,361 --> 00:07:25,231
Hyeon Cheol. What's up?

130
00:07:25,531 --> 00:07:28,231
I'm not at the store right now.
Do not go to the store, okay?

131
00:07:28,901 --> 00:07:30,671
This isn't something
I can say over the phone.

132
00:07:31,201 --> 00:07:33,041
Can we meet up for a bit?

133
00:07:33,841 --> 00:07:34,841
Okay.

134
00:07:35,441 --> 00:07:36,811
I'll call you back.

135
00:07:46,151 --> 00:07:49,521
- Dad, did the shoot go well?
- Yes, it was okay.

136
00:07:49,961 --> 00:07:51,361
You girls worked hard today.

137
00:07:51,691 --> 00:07:54,131
Thank you. We'll head on up now.

138
00:07:54,831 --> 00:07:55,901
Eun Bin.

139
00:07:56,331 --> 00:08:00,031
- Yes?
- Why did you call your mom earlier?

140
00:08:00,401 --> 00:08:02,671
I called her?
What are you talking about?

141
00:08:02,971 --> 00:08:05,071
- Did I call her?
- I don't know.

142
00:08:05,501 --> 00:08:06,671
Really?

143
00:08:07,111 --> 00:08:09,681
I guess I must have been mistaken.
Right.

144
00:08:09,941 --> 00:08:11,681
- Go on up and rest.
- Okay.

145
00:08:19,921 --> 00:08:21,221
(Taehan)

146
00:08:21,291 --> 00:08:23,791
I've revised the cue sheets
based on our meeting.

147
00:08:25,731 --> 00:08:30,261
What? If we cut all this,
won't the show feel a little empty?

148
00:08:30,961 --> 00:08:34,001
The point is to remove the theatrics
and focus on letting...

149
00:08:34,101 --> 00:08:35,471
the quality of the clothes shine.

150
00:08:36,001 --> 00:08:39,141
Yes, that's right. Like we've had
a big enough budget...

151
00:08:39,211 --> 00:08:40,271
to work with anyway.

152
00:08:42,841 --> 00:08:47,651
Sorry, I've been so on edge lately.
Let's get back to basics.

153
00:08:48,051 --> 00:08:49,051
Yes.

154
00:08:55,391 --> 00:08:59,061
Yes, sir. What? Really?

155
00:09:00,131 --> 00:09:01,361
I see.

156
00:09:01,891 --> 00:09:06,271
Got it.
Thank you so much. Right. Okay.

157
00:09:06,971 --> 00:09:10,401
What is it?
Are they bringing us pity snacks?

158
00:09:11,041 --> 00:09:15,681
No, they approved
our budget increase.

159
00:09:16,041 --> 00:09:17,541
- What?
- What?

160
00:09:17,611 --> 00:09:19,081
- Seriously?
- Oh, my.

161
00:09:19,151 --> 00:09:22,751
Director Yang said it'd pass easily,
and it really did.

162
00:09:23,751 --> 00:09:27,251
That's our Director Yang for you.
He's a man of his word.

163
00:09:28,751 --> 00:09:31,361
- Director!
- Ta-da!

164
00:09:31,421 --> 00:09:33,361
Director,
we heard the budget was approved.

165
00:09:34,191 --> 00:09:38,601
Darn, I wanted to surprise you.
Did Management already call?

166
00:09:38,661 --> 00:09:41,731
Yes. But, Director,
how did you even pull it off?

167
00:09:41,801 --> 00:09:46,111
What do you mean, how?
I confronted Director Baek head-on.

168
00:09:47,741 --> 00:09:52,111
Anyway, you can all relax now
and just concentrate on the work.

169
00:09:52,451 --> 00:09:53,911
- You got it!
- Okay!

170
00:09:54,011 --> 00:09:56,321
All right, I brought snacks!

171
00:09:57,051 --> 00:10:00,991
- This looks amazing. Thank you.
- Tteokbokki!

172
00:10:01,051 --> 00:10:03,891
- This is awesome.
- This is the best.

173
00:10:04,361 --> 00:10:06,691
Here you go. All right!

174
00:10:07,391 --> 00:10:08,491
- It's still warm.
- Here.

175
00:10:09,001 --> 00:10:11,061
- What's this?
- Have some tteokbokki.

176
00:10:11,131 --> 00:10:13,931
- Are these dumplings?
- This looks so good. Oh, man.

177
00:10:20,911 --> 00:10:23,241
Gosh, what are you doing,
Vice President?

178
00:10:28,851 --> 00:10:30,181
The condition
for the budget approval...

179
00:10:31,221 --> 00:10:32,991
is that Pacu Nacho has to resign.

180
00:10:33,821 --> 00:10:34,821
What?

181
00:10:35,491 --> 00:10:38,321
He made a deal with Director Baek,
putting his own job on the line.

182
00:10:39,661 --> 00:10:43,561
Wait, so you're saying
no matter how the show does,

183
00:10:43,831 --> 00:10:45,771
he's just going to quit?

184
00:10:50,901 --> 00:10:54,911
We'll stick with the lower budget.
We don't need their darn money.

185
00:10:56,141 --> 00:10:57,411
It's no use.

186
00:10:57,841 --> 00:11:00,981
They'll just find fault again,
saying the results are the same,

187
00:11:01,551 --> 00:11:04,221
and Pacu Nacho would end up
having to resign anyway.

188
00:11:04,721 --> 00:11:08,991
But he's just giving up like this,
without even putting up a fight?

189
00:11:09,221 --> 00:11:12,531
It's not just the Fashion Division.
He's giving up on Ju Ah, too.

190
00:11:12,891 --> 00:11:14,061
I understand why.

191
00:11:14,691 --> 00:11:17,231
Something major has come up
between them.

192
00:11:21,431 --> 00:11:24,101
Dr. Han Seong Mi has breast cancer.

193
00:11:26,941 --> 00:11:27,941
What?

194
00:11:29,011 --> 00:11:30,011
No...

195
00:11:32,141 --> 00:11:34,051
Wait, what do you mean?

196
00:11:36,581 --> 00:11:38,181
What stage?

197
00:11:39,191 --> 00:11:40,191
Stage two.

198
00:11:40,751 --> 00:11:42,391
We won't know for sure
until after the surgery, but...

199
00:11:43,461 --> 00:11:45,191
there are no guarantees.

200
00:11:46,391 --> 00:11:47,391
My gosh...

201
00:11:50,001 --> 00:11:51,901
Ju Ah doesn't know, does she?

202
00:11:53,631 --> 00:11:56,901
She asked that it be kept a secret
from Ms. Gong until after the show.

203
00:12:01,141 --> 00:12:02,641
This is insane.

204
00:12:16,161 --> 00:12:18,991
How on earth did you convince
Director Baek?

205
00:12:20,061 --> 00:12:22,661
- I just said what had to be said.
- Oh, my.

206
00:12:24,261 --> 00:12:28,501
Man, this fashion show
has been such a roller coaster.

207
00:12:28,671 --> 00:12:29,671
Right?

208
00:12:31,201 --> 00:12:33,311
How's Dr. Han been lately?

209
00:12:33,641 --> 00:12:37,841
She's full of energy. She's offering
counseling any chance she gets.

210
00:12:39,311 --> 00:12:42,721
She must feel a little lost,
resting after working so hard.

211
00:12:42,821 --> 00:12:46,151
I know. If she was going to do that,
why take a break in the first place?

212
00:12:46,451 --> 00:12:49,291
So be extra nice to your mom.

213
00:12:49,621 --> 00:12:50,821
Yes, I get it.

214
00:12:51,861 --> 00:12:54,031
I should go inside
before someone sees us.

215
00:12:54,691 --> 00:12:57,501
Right. We'll come in separately
tomorrow, too.

216
00:12:58,261 --> 00:12:59,271
Okay.

217
00:13:00,271 --> 00:13:03,071
- Don't pull another all-nighter.
- I'm pulling an all-nighter.

218
00:13:03,301 --> 00:13:05,841
Why? I got you the whole budget.

219
00:13:06,041 --> 00:13:10,611
Why do you think? If the show
goes badly, you might have to quit.

220
00:13:10,841 --> 00:13:13,611
How could it go wrong?
You're Gong Ju Ah.

221
00:13:14,511 --> 00:13:17,451
Anyway, I'm giving it my all,
so don't try to stop me.

222
00:13:18,551 --> 00:13:20,021
- I'm off.
- Okay.

223
00:13:24,321 --> 00:13:25,321
Get home safe.

224
00:13:49,281 --> 00:13:50,281
What are you doing here?

225
00:13:51,221 --> 00:13:52,421
Why are you here again
without calling?

226
00:13:54,521 --> 00:13:56,761
I have an early meeting
nearby tomorrow.

227
00:13:57,361 --> 00:13:58,361
Where's Mom?

228
00:13:59,261 --> 00:14:00,661
She was tired,
so she turned in early.

229
00:14:01,161 --> 00:14:02,491
She had a shoot today, too.

230
00:14:03,531 --> 00:14:06,701
Then why are you out here,
moping all by yourself?

231
00:14:07,371 --> 00:14:08,371
You...

232
00:14:09,401 --> 00:14:10,671
Don't you ever think
about your mother?

233
00:14:12,771 --> 00:14:15,341
Sometimes. Why?

234
00:14:16,041 --> 00:14:17,041
No reason, just...

235
00:14:17,841 --> 00:14:18,981
She just popped into my head.

236
00:14:21,211 --> 00:14:24,721
You two barely even talked,
so what is there to think about?

237
00:14:26,221 --> 00:14:27,521
That she cheated on me.

238
00:14:28,321 --> 00:14:31,121
For a while,
I knew she was making secret calls,

239
00:14:32,491 --> 00:14:33,961
but honestly,
I didn't pay it any mind.

240
00:14:35,131 --> 00:14:37,161
I just figured she made a new friend
or something.

241
00:14:38,631 --> 00:14:40,131
Then suddenly, she was gone.

242
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:42,471
And I was served
with divorce papers.

243
00:14:44,741 --> 00:14:46,941
I'd never been a suspicious person,

244
00:14:48,411 --> 00:14:49,841
and I haven't been the same since.

245
00:14:51,381 --> 00:14:55,911
So is that why you've been tracking
Stepmother's location for 15 years?

246
00:14:57,381 --> 00:14:58,681
You do trust her, right?

247
00:15:00,321 --> 00:15:01,321
I do.

248
00:15:02,621 --> 00:15:03,621
Too much, in fact.

249
00:15:05,191 --> 00:15:06,491
And that's what scares me.

250
00:15:07,591 --> 00:15:11,031
Do you get anxious
when you can't see her...

251
00:15:11,131 --> 00:15:12,261
while she's working?

252
00:15:14,631 --> 00:15:15,631
I guess so.

253
00:15:19,041 --> 00:15:20,811
It's called abandonment anxiety.

254
00:15:22,241 --> 00:15:25,081
I was also afraid
of being abandoned again,

255
00:15:25,781 --> 00:15:27,611
so I ran away to study abroad,

256
00:15:28,451 --> 00:15:30,951
And Eun Bin was also scared
of being abandoned again,

257
00:15:31,281 --> 00:15:33,421
so she tried to keep her distance
from Mom.

258
00:15:34,951 --> 00:15:36,421
The saying, "Time heals all wounds."

259
00:15:38,261 --> 00:15:39,661
That's a total lie, isn't it?

260
00:15:41,291 --> 00:15:42,291
Well...

261
00:15:43,931 --> 00:15:46,901
Would you consider going to therapy?

262
00:15:50,501 --> 00:15:51,541
No.

263
00:15:52,741 --> 00:15:53,841
I'll try to control myself.

264
00:15:56,811 --> 00:15:58,381
I think the alcohol
is making it worse.

265
00:16:00,811 --> 00:16:01,811
Go to bed.

266
00:16:03,081 --> 00:16:04,281
Wait, but...

267
00:16:13,031 --> 00:16:14,061
Hyun Bin, you're here a lot lately.

268
00:16:15,061 --> 00:16:17,361
Yes, I guess.
I have things to do in the morning.

269
00:16:17,931 --> 00:16:21,201
With Hyun Bin around so much,
I should save up and move out soon.

270
00:16:22,201 --> 00:16:26,171
I'm moving back home soon,
so you could just take my room.

271
00:16:26,771 --> 00:16:28,741
Right. That's a wonderful idea.

272
00:16:29,311 --> 00:16:31,241
That's okay.
Let Ji Hu have the room.

273
00:16:31,611 --> 00:16:34,681
I think I'll be heading back
to Argentina.

274
00:16:34,951 --> 00:16:36,581
Oh, my goodness, Hyun Bin.

275
00:16:36,851 --> 00:16:38,681
What are you talking about
all of a sudden?

276
00:16:39,021 --> 00:16:41,721
Didn't you sign a one-year contract
with Taehan Group?

277
00:16:42,521 --> 00:16:44,121
It hasn't been anywhere near
a year yet.

278
00:16:44,891 --> 00:16:46,591
Things have changed.

279
00:16:46,961 --> 00:16:48,761
Wait, when?

280
00:16:49,331 --> 00:16:50,401
I'm planning on leaving soon.

281
00:16:50,761 --> 00:16:53,401
I'm handing over my work
and tying up loose ends.

282
00:16:55,601 --> 00:16:59,101
Even if I go,
I won't just disappear like before.

283
00:16:59,441 --> 00:17:03,481
I'll come over a lot and spend time
with you all before I leave.

284
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:06,951
But I thought you said
there's a woman you like.

285
00:17:07,251 --> 00:17:08,551
Are you really just going
to leave like that?

286
00:17:09,211 --> 00:17:10,281
You're not going to marry her?

287
00:17:11,651 --> 00:17:14,521
No. I figured you'd all be
against it anyway.

288
00:17:15,191 --> 00:17:16,691
Oh, Hyun Bin.

289
00:17:17,191 --> 00:17:18,291
You punk.

290
00:17:18,421 --> 00:17:21,431
Who is she? Why would we object?
Is she a foreigner?

291
00:17:22,691 --> 00:17:26,471
Hey, if you love her,
who cares if she's our sworn enemy?

292
00:17:26,971 --> 00:17:30,571
My goodness, what are you saying?
Don't speak that into existence!

293
00:17:31,441 --> 00:17:34,641
What are you talking about?
I was just making a point.

294
00:17:36,041 --> 00:17:37,041
Yes.

295
00:17:56,731 --> 00:17:59,571
Eun Bin, I hear you'll work
part-time at your mom's shop.

296
00:18:00,171 --> 00:18:03,071
Stop by now and then.
I'll treat you to some barbecue.

297
00:18:17,981 --> 00:18:20,121
She's not replying.
What's gotten into her?

298
00:18:20,491 --> 00:18:21,851
I wonder
if something's really wrong.

299
00:18:22,991 --> 00:18:24,491
Woo Jae, are you off to work?

300
00:18:24,821 --> 00:18:28,191
- Want me to make you breakfast?
- No, Mom. I'm late and have to go.

301
00:18:30,531 --> 00:18:33,831
He said he was happy I was home,
but I barely even see him.

302
00:18:37,571 --> 00:18:38,641
Who's this from?

303
00:18:41,211 --> 00:18:45,281
"Information regarding your
admission and surgery schedule."

304
00:18:49,051 --> 00:18:50,921
Right, I should probably pack.

305
00:18:52,281 --> 00:18:53,851
Hold on. What do I need?

306
00:18:54,751 --> 00:18:57,821
Toiletries, a book, what else...

307
00:19:01,691 --> 00:19:03,761
Director Yang.
To what do I owe the call?

308
00:19:04,361 --> 00:19:05,401
Are you at home?

309
00:19:05,831 --> 00:19:07,431
Yes, I am. Why?

310
00:19:08,231 --> 00:19:10,501
I was just calling to see
how you're feeling.

311
00:19:11,641 --> 00:19:12,741
I'm fine.

312
00:19:13,071 --> 00:19:16,281
It won't interfere with the show,
so you don't need to worry.

313
00:19:16,841 --> 00:19:20,051
I should've seen it through.
I'm sorry.

314
00:19:20,151 --> 00:19:21,151
Forget it.

315
00:19:21,211 --> 00:19:25,181
I can't owe you again only to get
lectured by your mother.

316
00:19:26,191 --> 00:19:28,491
Again, I'm truly sorry about that.

317
00:19:29,051 --> 00:19:31,621
It's fine.
It wasn't your fault anyway.

318
00:19:32,291 --> 00:19:33,791
I'll see you at the final fitting.

319
00:19:34,061 --> 00:19:38,731
Could you step outside for a moment?
I left something for you.

320
00:19:39,971 --> 00:19:41,271
What is it?

321
00:19:52,341 --> 00:19:53,481
What is all this?

322
00:19:57,181 --> 00:19:59,021
Toiletries,

323
00:20:00,021 --> 00:20:01,351
a tumbler with a straw,

324
00:20:02,221 --> 00:20:03,561
a cushion, a book.

325
00:20:05,221 --> 00:20:09,031
My, it's like
he was eavesdropping on me.

326
00:20:12,631 --> 00:20:16,031
- You're all set. Bye. Thank you.
- Thank you.

327
00:20:17,601 --> 00:20:18,641
Hello.

328
00:20:19,711 --> 00:20:22,371
What brings you here?

329
00:20:22,671 --> 00:20:23,841
Why do you ask?

330
00:20:24,511 --> 00:20:26,181
What's wrong with me stopping by?

331
00:20:27,611 --> 00:20:29,151
Ju Ah told me.

332
00:20:30,021 --> 00:20:31,581
That if the fashion show
is a failure,

333
00:20:32,281 --> 00:20:33,991
you might lose your job, right?

334
00:20:35,091 --> 00:20:38,761
The fashion show
isn't going to fail.

335
00:20:39,121 --> 00:20:40,531
Ju Ah is doing a great job.

336
00:20:41,531 --> 00:20:43,531
So you're saying you two
aren't going to break up?

337
00:20:44,661 --> 00:20:45,961
After the fashion show,

338
00:20:46,871 --> 00:20:50,341
you're still set on telling Dr. Han
about your relationship?

339
00:20:51,471 --> 00:20:55,171
No.
Even if the show's a success, I...

340
00:20:56,581 --> 00:20:58,111
I'm planning to leave for Argentina.

341
00:20:58,541 --> 00:20:59,751
What? You're what?

342
00:21:00,511 --> 00:21:02,951
Wait, what are you talking about?

343
00:21:04,121 --> 00:21:07,451
I told you two to break up,
not for you to leave Korea!

344
00:21:08,351 --> 00:21:11,191
Gosh, this puts me
in a really tough spot.

345
00:21:11,821 --> 00:21:13,561
You saw your family again
after so long.

346
00:21:13,561 --> 00:21:14,931
Do you want me to take the blame?

347
00:21:15,731 --> 00:21:18,531
No one in my family will know why.

348
00:21:19,831 --> 00:21:23,271
Then you should just stay
at the company!

349
00:21:23,541 --> 00:21:25,441
I think it'd be too hard for us...

350
00:21:25,641 --> 00:21:27,541
to keep working together
after breaking up.

351
00:21:28,571 --> 00:21:30,481
For goodness' sake...
This is absurd.

352
00:21:31,141 --> 00:21:33,811
What about Ju Ah? Does she know?

353
00:21:35,151 --> 00:21:36,151
No.

354
00:21:36,521 --> 00:21:38,821
I'm planning to tell her
after the show.

355
00:21:39,921 --> 00:21:43,221
She's going to be devastated
when she finds out about Dr. Han,

356
00:21:43,291 --> 00:21:46,091
and I won't be there to comfort her.

357
00:21:46,261 --> 00:21:48,731
So I was hoping
you could look after her.

358
00:21:51,601 --> 00:21:54,971
I've arranged for the family seats
to be right in the front row,

359
00:21:55,031 --> 00:21:56,501
so please come
and show your support.

360
00:21:56,841 --> 00:21:59,771
She wants you to see Dr. Han...

361
00:21:59,841 --> 00:22:02,941
walking down the runway
in the clothes she made.

362
00:22:03,411 --> 00:22:04,841
It's Ju Ah's dream.

363
00:22:09,451 --> 00:22:10,921
My gosh.

364
00:22:28,671 --> 00:22:29,671
Hey, Dong Suk.

365
00:22:30,571 --> 00:22:31,741
You haven't left for work yet,
have you?

366
00:22:33,541 --> 00:22:36,211
Listen, there's something
I need to talk to you about.

367
00:22:36,581 --> 00:22:37,581
Is that Dae Han?

368
00:22:38,911 --> 00:22:40,311
You're not with Hui Gyeong, are you?

369
00:22:41,051 --> 00:22:42,851
Yes. I'll call you back in a bit.

370
00:22:43,221 --> 00:22:45,651
Where are you? Tell me.

371
00:22:46,221 --> 00:22:47,351
The teahouse in the market?

372
00:22:48,021 --> 00:22:49,151
I'm on my way there now.

373
00:22:49,421 --> 00:22:52,591
Don't listen to her!
You need to hear my side first.

374
00:22:52,661 --> 00:22:53,961
Dong Suk, I'll be right there!

375
00:22:59,301 --> 00:23:00,531
Why did you ask to see me?

376
00:23:01,071 --> 00:23:04,741
Haven't you heard from Ji Hu's dad?
I'm sure you heard we broke up.

377
00:23:05,041 --> 00:23:06,141
Hey.

378
00:23:06,811 --> 00:23:09,781
You're younger than me.
How dare you talk to me like that?

379
00:23:10,011 --> 00:23:12,211
I'd say we're past formalities,
don't you think?

380
00:23:12,341 --> 00:23:13,851
You want another beating, don't you?

381
00:23:13,851 --> 00:23:15,911
- I will pull your hair out!
- Ma'am.

382
00:23:20,191 --> 00:23:21,521
Answer my question.

383
00:23:22,151 --> 00:23:23,261
Why did you ask to see me?

384
00:23:24,161 --> 00:23:26,861
I gave Ji Hu's dad back to you.
Now, break up with Dae Han.

385
00:23:27,061 --> 00:23:29,901
- What was that? You little...
- I'm pregnant.

386
00:23:30,831 --> 00:23:34,771
What? Who's the father?
But he had a vasectomy...

387
00:23:38,571 --> 00:23:39,841
Don't tell me...

388
00:23:40,811 --> 00:23:44,481
Are you saying you're pregnant
with Gong Dae Han's child?

389
00:23:44,941 --> 00:23:45,941
Yes.

390
00:23:46,211 --> 00:23:49,211
You know how much
Dae Han loves children,

391
00:23:49,711 --> 00:23:50,721
and how badly
he's always wanted one.

392
00:23:51,681 --> 00:23:52,681
Break up with him.

393
00:23:53,491 --> 00:23:54,851
For his sake.

394
00:23:56,191 --> 00:23:58,661
Dong Suk!

395
00:24:00,261 --> 00:24:01,261
Dong Suk!

396
00:24:02,631 --> 00:24:03,631
Are you okay?

397
00:24:03,931 --> 00:24:06,231
I told her to break up with you.

398
00:24:07,201 --> 00:24:08,731
Why on earth are you doing this?

399
00:24:09,371 --> 00:24:11,241
What is it you want? Money?

400
00:24:12,001 --> 00:24:13,241
A father.

401
00:24:13,841 --> 00:24:14,911
A father for my baby.

402
00:24:15,241 --> 00:24:16,271
Don't be ridiculous.

403
00:24:16,881 --> 00:24:18,981
Whether you have that baby or not
is none of my business.

404
00:24:19,781 --> 00:24:22,351
That's a lie.
You're not the irresponsible type.

405
00:24:22,751 --> 00:24:25,621
If you won't do it,
I'll tell your mother and Seong Mi.

406
00:24:25,681 --> 00:24:26,791
Will you shut your mouth?

407
00:24:27,351 --> 00:24:29,891
Just try contacting my family.
I swear you won't get away with it.

408
00:24:29,961 --> 00:24:30,961
Understand?

409
00:24:37,731 --> 00:24:38,901
You two talk.

410
00:24:40,131 --> 00:24:41,131
I'll just...

411
00:24:41,401 --> 00:24:42,401
Dong Suk.

412
00:24:48,741 --> 00:24:49,741
I...

413
00:24:50,341 --> 00:24:52,541
I have to open the restaurant.

414
00:25:26,481 --> 00:25:29,411
Seriously, calm down.

415
00:25:29,781 --> 00:25:31,281
You're going to startle the baby.

416
00:25:33,021 --> 00:25:36,891
Let's put the past behind us,
darling.

417
00:25:37,421 --> 00:25:39,861
Stuff happens in life, right?

418
00:25:41,431 --> 00:25:42,591
Call me when the baby's born.

419
00:25:44,201 --> 00:25:45,731
I'll send you child support.

420
00:25:50,141 --> 00:25:51,701
Even if you hate me,

421
00:25:52,471 --> 00:25:54,571
you can't hate our child.

422
00:25:55,571 --> 00:25:56,641
The baby...

423
00:25:57,581 --> 00:25:59,581
can hear everything
from inside my womb.

424
00:26:07,721 --> 00:26:09,321
I'll give you one more day.

425
00:26:10,021 --> 00:26:12,621
If I don't hear from you by then,

426
00:26:12,721 --> 00:26:15,391
I'm telling your mother or Seong Mi.

427
00:26:22,171 --> 00:26:24,441
- Here, you do it.
- Eun Bin.

428
00:26:24,541 --> 00:26:27,271
- Clean this up properly.
- No, you do it!

429
00:26:27,271 --> 00:26:28,541
You're getting dust everywhere!

430
00:26:29,341 --> 00:26:30,341
All right, I'll do it.

431
00:26:35,051 --> 00:26:37,551
If it's hard to stay in touch,
you don't have to.

432
00:26:37,981 --> 00:26:39,881
I won't reach out anymore either.

433
00:26:40,421 --> 00:26:41,951
- I'm sorry.
- Eun Bin, is this good enough?

434
00:26:41,951 --> 00:26:44,921
- Who threw trash here?
- Eun Bin, is this okay?

435
00:26:44,991 --> 00:26:47,691
- All done? Thanks!
- Yes. I'll get the rest.

436
00:26:47,761 --> 00:26:48,761
All right.

437
00:26:52,031 --> 00:26:53,031
Oh, right.

438
00:26:54,301 --> 00:26:56,871
Mom,
did we talk on the phone yesterday?

439
00:26:57,401 --> 00:26:58,641
No, why?

440
00:26:59,271 --> 00:27:01,471
Dad was asking
if I had talked to you.

441
00:27:02,071 --> 00:27:03,271
Oh, did he?

442
00:27:04,411 --> 00:27:05,981
He must've gotten it mixed up.

443
00:27:06,441 --> 00:27:07,611
That's weird.

444
00:27:18,191 --> 00:27:20,491
Dad, I...

445
00:27:21,391 --> 00:27:22,961
I think
I should get some herbal medicine.

446
00:27:23,561 --> 00:27:25,601
Why? What's wrong?

447
00:27:26,261 --> 00:27:28,601
It's just... I keep...

448
00:27:29,431 --> 00:27:31,001
getting these anxious thoughts.

449
00:27:36,511 --> 00:27:38,181
That's because
your liver's qi is stagnant.

450
00:27:38,711 --> 00:27:40,781
We have to ground
your scattered energy.

451
00:27:41,981 --> 00:27:45,251
But what are you so anxious about?

452
00:27:45,621 --> 00:27:46,621
Oh, well...

453
00:27:47,521 --> 00:27:49,091
No reason in particular.

454
00:27:55,891 --> 00:27:57,731
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

455
00:28:05,601 --> 00:28:07,211
Instead of worrying like this,

456
00:28:07,811 --> 00:28:09,741
should I just turn
her location tracking back on?

457
00:28:17,881 --> 00:28:19,421
Hello? Hey, Se Ri.

458
00:28:20,351 --> 00:28:22,051
I just had lunch with my dad.

459
00:28:22,521 --> 00:28:25,021
Honey,
aren't you wondering what I'm up to?

460
00:28:25,621 --> 00:28:27,661
Want to video chat?

461
00:28:27,931 --> 00:28:30,031
What? No.

462
00:28:30,101 --> 00:28:31,931
A video call?
You're in the middle of work.

463
00:28:33,601 --> 00:28:37,441
The girls are here,
and I wanted you to see me at work.

464
00:28:37,601 --> 00:28:38,771
That's okay.

465
00:28:39,171 --> 00:28:42,311
I can picture it perfectly
just by hearing your voice.

466
00:28:43,711 --> 00:28:47,281
Okay.
You'll pick me up after work, right?

467
00:28:47,711 --> 00:28:49,551
Should I?

468
00:28:50,981 --> 00:28:52,481
We can have
a little after-work date.

469
00:28:52,881 --> 00:28:54,551
Okay. See you later, then.

470
00:29:03,231 --> 00:29:04,231
Hyeon Cheol.

471
00:29:04,531 --> 00:29:07,371
Today and tomorrow are
probably not going to work for me.

472
00:29:07,801 --> 00:29:08,971
I'll be in touch.

473
00:29:14,011 --> 00:29:17,581
(Ms. Jo Hyeon Suk)

474
00:29:17,641 --> 00:29:18,681
(Save)

475
00:29:19,341 --> 00:29:20,751
(Ms. Jo Hyeon Suk)

476
00:29:27,551 --> 00:29:28,551
(3 messages selected)

477
00:29:36,591 --> 00:29:38,801
Please keep this a secret
until I'm gone.

478
00:29:40,031 --> 00:29:43,871
No one in the Fashion Division
can know, including Ju Ah.

479
00:29:46,471 --> 00:29:47,471
Understood.

480
00:29:48,711 --> 00:29:51,681
Okay, here's the global buyer list,

481
00:29:51,741 --> 00:29:56,251
protocols for each country,
and the reorder strategy I made.

482
00:30:01,351 --> 00:30:04,521
Wait...
I get leaving the company, but...

483
00:30:05,321 --> 00:30:07,891
are you really going to be able to
break up with Ju Ah?

484
00:30:18,571 --> 00:30:19,901
What are you doing here?

485
00:30:20,271 --> 00:30:23,271
Oh, man.
He's giving me so much work.

486
00:30:23,471 --> 00:30:24,481
Goodness.

487
00:30:24,641 --> 00:30:26,281
You have just as much work
coming your way, Ms. Gong.

488
00:30:26,611 --> 00:30:28,881
Don't even think about relaxing
after the fashion show.

489
00:30:29,681 --> 00:30:31,481
What do you mean?
I'm planning on taking a vacation.

490
00:30:31,881 --> 00:30:33,451
Why? What kind of work
are you going to give me?

491
00:30:33,721 --> 00:30:37,161
I've set up an exclusive interview
with L'dor Magazine.

492
00:30:38,121 --> 00:30:39,121
Me?

493
00:30:40,091 --> 00:30:43,091
But they don't just interview
anyone.

494
00:30:43,161 --> 00:30:47,571
What do you mean, "anyone?"
You're one of Taehan's top stars.

495
00:30:48,201 --> 00:30:53,141
The angle is "young female director
who managed design and production."

496
00:30:53,341 --> 00:30:56,841
The magazine will send guidelines,
so be prepared.

497
00:30:57,681 --> 00:30:59,441
But what if the fashion show
is a disaster?

498
00:30:59,911 --> 00:31:02,111
- Then what will happen?
- There you go again.

499
00:31:02,481 --> 00:31:03,981
I told you, have some confidence.

500
00:31:06,281 --> 00:31:08,351
Right. Understood.

501
00:31:08,721 --> 00:31:10,051
You'll do great.

502
00:31:23,371 --> 00:31:28,041
- Let me get your jacket, CEO Cha.
- Honey. Thank you.

503
00:31:29,111 --> 00:31:31,711
Honey, after work tomorrow,

504
00:31:31,711 --> 00:31:33,041
I'm meeting
with the other doctors' wives.

505
00:31:33,541 --> 00:31:34,551
Really?

506
00:31:34,951 --> 00:31:38,321
- So suddenly?
- It's been scheduled for weeks,

507
00:31:38,351 --> 00:31:41,351
but you know how crazy it's been
with the shoot and store opening.

508
00:31:41,421 --> 00:31:45,061
But the treasurer called
and reminded me last night.

509
00:31:45,391 --> 00:31:46,691
I see.

510
00:31:47,661 --> 00:31:50,431
Actually, it's a perfect chance
to promote the new store.

511
00:31:50,801 --> 00:31:54,071
You go shower first.
I'll get Father a late-night snack.

512
00:31:54,201 --> 00:31:55,201
All right?

513
00:32:15,991 --> 00:32:17,061
Do you want anything...

514
00:32:20,731 --> 00:32:21,731
Honey.

515
00:32:22,361 --> 00:32:23,661
I guess I'm getting paranoid again.

516
00:32:24,201 --> 00:32:25,201
I'm sorry.

517
00:32:27,101 --> 00:32:29,431
Do you feel better
now that you've checked?

518
00:32:29,971 --> 00:32:32,271
What? Yes.

519
00:32:32,641 --> 00:32:34,611
You talked with Ms. Jo Hyeon Suk.

520
00:32:35,211 --> 00:32:37,511
But yesterday, you said
you talked to Eun Bin.

521
00:32:38,081 --> 00:32:40,681
So I asked her, and she said
you two hadn't spoken.

522
00:32:41,611 --> 00:32:44,551
So I guess that's why
I thought you were lying.

523
00:32:45,651 --> 00:32:50,191
It's my fault. I was so out of it,
I just answered without thinking.

524
00:32:50,821 --> 00:32:53,991
Look,
I'm not suspicious of you, okay?

525
00:32:55,091 --> 00:32:57,301
I don't know why.
It just came over me.

526
00:32:57,661 --> 00:32:58,661
I'm so sorry.

527
00:33:00,671 --> 00:33:04,371
There's nothing to be sorry about.
I know exactly why you get this way.

528
00:33:05,341 --> 00:33:06,341
Se Ri.

529
00:33:07,241 --> 00:33:10,941
You can check my phone anytime.
Turn my location tracker back on.

530
00:33:11,111 --> 00:33:12,111
All right?

531
00:33:16,681 --> 00:33:17,681
It's okay.

532
00:33:19,351 --> 00:33:20,421
(A Hint of Spring)

533
00:33:21,791 --> 00:33:23,091
Even this book is boring.

534
00:33:24,021 --> 00:33:26,721
It was so much more fun
when I could only sneak a few pages.

535
00:33:32,031 --> 00:33:35,171
Of all days, the kids are late,
and what's taking him so long?

536
00:33:37,371 --> 00:33:40,071
Hey, why are you still up?

537
00:33:40,811 --> 00:33:41,811
Were you waiting up for me?

538
00:33:42,171 --> 00:33:43,341
As if.

539
00:33:44,141 --> 00:33:45,311
So what kept you so late?

540
00:33:45,911 --> 00:33:50,311
Oh, I got an offer to give a lecture
at Mirae Bank.

541
00:33:50,781 --> 00:33:54,951
They want me to talk to VIP clients
about metabolic disorder prevention.

542
00:33:55,591 --> 00:33:58,591
But you had a morning meeting too.
You must be exhausted.

543
00:33:58,921 --> 00:34:00,831
Tell me about it.

544
00:34:01,361 --> 00:34:05,861
With my practice and these events...
I can barely think straight.

545
00:34:06,501 --> 00:34:10,901
I don't know how you've kept it up.
Seriously.

546
00:34:11,371 --> 00:34:13,441
I'm going to wash up.

547
00:34:14,841 --> 00:34:16,171
Hey, honey.

548
00:34:16,841 --> 00:34:18,111
What did you do today?

549
00:34:19,441 --> 00:34:21,681
I worked on the fashion show...

550
00:34:22,511 --> 00:34:24,051
and packed my hospital bag.

551
00:34:25,151 --> 00:34:28,451
You won't be able to get around
for a while after the surgery.

552
00:34:28,721 --> 00:34:32,421
What if we go somewhere
this weekend? Get some fresh air?

553
00:34:32,861 --> 00:34:33,861
Forget it.

554
00:34:34,191 --> 00:34:36,731
Since when have we ever done
things like that?

555
00:34:38,201 --> 00:34:41,201
But after the fashion show,

556
00:34:41,571 --> 00:34:43,971
you're going to tell the kids
right away, aren't you?

557
00:34:45,341 --> 00:34:46,401
I have to.

558
00:34:46,971 --> 00:34:49,171
My surgery is right after the show.

559
00:34:50,941 --> 00:34:52,111
I'm going to bed.

560
00:34:52,981 --> 00:34:54,351
Okay.

561
00:35:05,761 --> 00:35:09,131
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

562
00:35:12,731 --> 00:35:13,931
Excuse me, Ms. Yang.

563
00:35:15,301 --> 00:35:16,831
Is something wrong?

564
00:35:17,371 --> 00:35:18,741
You've been sighing all day.

565
00:35:22,071 --> 00:35:23,071
Listen.

566
00:35:23,411 --> 00:35:26,241
You haven't heard from your family,
have you?

567
00:35:26,911 --> 00:35:27,911
From my family?

568
00:35:28,311 --> 00:35:29,311
Yes.

569
00:35:32,051 --> 00:35:33,321
No, nothing.

570
00:35:35,521 --> 00:35:36,621
Okay, got it.

571
00:35:38,321 --> 00:35:39,821
Let's hurry and close up
so we can head home.

572
00:35:41,061 --> 00:35:42,061
Okay.

573
00:35:54,741 --> 00:35:57,611
Dae Han.
Let's meet briefly tomorrow.

574
00:35:58,041 --> 00:35:59,511
There's something
I need to talk to you about.

575
00:36:25,171 --> 00:36:26,271
Why is the edge...

576
00:36:28,711 --> 00:36:29,941
Why is this so crooked?

577
00:36:34,011 --> 00:36:36,911
Two, two, three, four,

578
00:36:37,181 --> 00:36:40,251
five, six, seven, eight.

579
00:36:40,481 --> 00:36:44,691
All right, great job, everyone.
May you all prosper!

580
00:36:51,201 --> 00:36:54,571
Hey, let's hope we prosper too.

581
00:36:56,531 --> 00:36:57,641
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

582
00:36:57,741 --> 00:37:00,071
- I hope you go broke.
- "Prosper," my foot.

583
00:37:02,341 --> 00:37:04,681
Nurse Oh, I was wondering...

584
00:37:05,111 --> 00:37:06,141
Are you interested in a blind date?

585
00:37:06,211 --> 00:37:07,211
Sorry?

586
00:37:07,211 --> 00:37:11,521
My grandson saw you on TV
and said he really likes you.

587
00:37:13,121 --> 00:37:14,721
So, think about it...

588
00:37:15,091 --> 00:37:17,691
- and let me know, okay?
- Okay. Get home safe.

589
00:37:18,791 --> 00:37:21,291
- You scared me.
- Why didn't you just say no?

590
00:37:21,561 --> 00:37:24,431
I was just caught off guard.

591
00:37:26,361 --> 00:37:28,431
From now on,
you must turn them down.

592
00:37:28,701 --> 00:37:29,801
No, scratch that.

593
00:37:29,801 --> 00:37:32,971
Jin Ah, no more outside contact.
Go inside.

594
00:37:33,041 --> 00:37:34,041
Come on.

595
00:37:35,341 --> 00:37:36,341
All right, I get it.

596
00:37:41,851 --> 00:37:42,911
My goodness.

597
00:37:44,481 --> 00:37:46,081
- Officer Jung.
- Yes?

598
00:37:46,281 --> 00:37:47,321
Do you have a second?

599
00:37:50,051 --> 00:37:51,561
I'm sorry to have to show you this.

600
00:37:52,391 --> 00:37:56,331
It's fine. As a police officer,
I've seen it all.

601
00:37:57,131 --> 00:38:00,731
Besides, you're my Cupid.
Of course, I have to help you.

602
00:38:01,931 --> 00:38:03,831
What happens if she's lying?

603
00:38:04,871 --> 00:38:05,941
Listen carefully.

604
00:38:06,041 --> 00:38:10,441
If she's lying to make you liable
and threatens you, that's blackmail.

605
00:38:11,081 --> 00:38:14,881
If she demands money and gets it,
that constitutes fraud.

606
00:38:15,851 --> 00:38:18,551
Fraud related to pregnancy carries
a very heavy sentence.

607
00:38:19,221 --> 00:38:23,151
What do you think, Officer Jung?
It looks like this part here...

608
00:38:23,491 --> 00:38:26,091
is where the mother's
or the hospital's name was.

609
00:38:26,191 --> 00:38:27,831
I'm pretty sure it was cut off.

610
00:38:32,201 --> 00:38:35,931
You can't conclude it's fake
just because it's cut.

611
00:38:36,301 --> 00:38:40,271
Ask her for the original file
or the hospital records.

612
00:38:40,911 --> 00:38:41,911
Right.

613
00:38:42,971 --> 00:38:44,711
The ultrasound data
would still be on file.

614
00:38:45,641 --> 00:38:49,011
Exactly. And one more thing.

615
00:38:49,711 --> 00:38:50,721
What is it?

616
00:38:51,781 --> 00:38:52,781
What?

617
00:38:55,191 --> 00:38:56,591
Why did you ask to meet
on the street?

618
00:38:59,921 --> 00:39:01,131
(Women's Hospital
and Fertility Clinic)

619
00:39:01,131 --> 00:39:02,391
(Onjeong OB-GYN Clinic)

620
00:39:02,791 --> 00:39:03,791
What... What is this?

621
00:39:04,461 --> 00:39:07,731
To check on the baby.
I want to hear the heartbeat too.

622
00:39:08,731 --> 00:39:10,771
- What?
- Let's go inside.

623
00:39:12,071 --> 00:39:15,241
- Come on.
- Wait, are you doubting me?

624
00:39:15,641 --> 00:39:17,811
Let go of me. I'm offended.
I'm leaving.

625
00:39:17,881 --> 00:39:19,911
- Come on, let's go inside and see.
- No, let go!

626
00:39:20,911 --> 00:39:21,981
Hey!

627
00:39:22,051 --> 00:39:23,051
No, wait, hold on.

628
00:39:23,551 --> 00:39:28,291
What's there to be offended about?
Of course, we must check. Let's go.

629
00:39:29,751 --> 00:39:31,491
- Come on!
- No! I don't want to... My gosh!

630
00:39:31,591 --> 00:39:33,561
Hey, what's with you?
Why are you acting like a liar?

631
00:39:34,931 --> 00:39:36,161
Fine, I lied.

632
00:39:36,961 --> 00:39:37,961
What's a lie?

633
00:39:38,801 --> 00:39:41,931
That it's not my baby?
Or the whole pregnancy's a lie?

634
00:39:43,931 --> 00:39:45,071
I'm not pregnant.

635
00:39:48,041 --> 00:39:49,211
I can't believe you.

636
00:39:56,081 --> 00:39:57,851
(Onjeong OB-GYN Clinic)

637
00:39:58,351 --> 00:39:59,481
Where did you get this?

638
00:40:01,121 --> 00:40:04,321
I found it when I went to the OB-GYN
to get birth control pills.

639
00:40:05,021 --> 00:40:06,591
Why in the world
would you do that? Why?

640
00:40:07,121 --> 00:40:08,461
Because you broke up
with Ji Hu's dad...

641
00:40:08,631 --> 00:40:10,931
and were worried about getting by,
you tried to shake me down for cash?

642
00:40:11,131 --> 00:40:14,171
I don't need your money.
I make enough from my salon.

643
00:40:14,231 --> 00:40:15,531
Then why did you do it? Why?

644
00:40:17,271 --> 00:40:18,671
I watched "Human Theater."

645
00:40:22,071 --> 00:40:24,681
It made me fight with Ji Hu's dad
all the time.

646
00:40:25,281 --> 00:40:28,851
He was missing his home and child,
and so was I.

647
00:40:29,551 --> 00:40:31,681
The home I lived in,
the family I lived with...

648
00:40:33,021 --> 00:40:35,451
I wanted to be there too, you know.

649
00:40:38,091 --> 00:40:39,091
So?

650
00:40:40,621 --> 00:40:42,091
So you faked a pregnancy?

651
00:40:42,491 --> 00:40:45,861
It was the only way
you'd take me back.

652
00:40:45,861 --> 00:40:48,671
So you didn't think you'd be caught?
Is that it?

653
00:40:49,401 --> 00:40:52,971
I planned to wait for the right time
and lie that I'd had a miscarriage.

654
00:40:54,471 --> 00:40:55,471
What did you say?

655
00:40:56,111 --> 00:40:57,741
I said I was planning to lie.

656
00:41:01,711 --> 00:41:05,151
Wow, how sneaky. You recorded me?
What are you going to do with this?

657
00:41:05,221 --> 00:41:06,481
Are you going to sue me
or something?

658
00:41:06,651 --> 00:41:09,591
It's to defend us, not attack you.
Understand?

659
00:41:11,521 --> 00:41:12,521
Can I really...

660
00:41:13,391 --> 00:41:16,891
- not move back into your house?
- No.

661
00:41:17,491 --> 00:41:18,501
You cannot.

662
00:41:18,831 --> 00:41:20,531
Do you really love her?

663
00:41:21,871 --> 00:41:22,871
Yes, I do.

664
00:41:25,041 --> 00:41:28,141
That's ridiculous.
Don't you know it's not meant to be?

665
00:41:28,241 --> 00:41:31,311
You knew you shouldn't be together,
but you did it anyway, didn't you?

666
00:41:31,781 --> 00:41:34,011
Don't ever contact me again.
Or else,

667
00:41:35,811 --> 00:41:37,721
we'll meet at the police station.
Got it?

668
00:41:40,951 --> 00:41:41,951
Wait...

669
00:42:02,571 --> 00:42:04,411
- Dong Suk.
- That woman...

670
00:42:05,941 --> 00:42:07,141
If she has the baby,

671
00:42:10,851 --> 00:42:11,951
I'll raise it.

672
00:42:13,721 --> 00:42:14,721
What?

673
00:42:15,051 --> 00:42:16,391
Tell her to have the baby.

674
00:42:17,051 --> 00:42:19,691
And then we'll take the baby in.
Okay? All right?

675
00:42:25,061 --> 00:42:26,761
You think this is funny right now?

676
00:42:28,171 --> 00:42:29,471
No, that's not it...

677
00:42:30,771 --> 00:42:32,171
There has to be a baby to raise one.

678
00:42:33,801 --> 00:42:34,811
What do you mean?

679
00:42:35,971 --> 00:42:36,971
It was all a lie.

680
00:42:42,181 --> 00:42:43,611
That horrible witch.

681
00:42:44,681 --> 00:42:46,781
How can she jerk people around
like this?

682
00:42:47,581 --> 00:42:50,851
How could she keep doing this,
knowing it's your biggest weakness?

683
00:42:52,261 --> 00:42:53,461
Gosh, that witch.

684
00:42:55,461 --> 00:42:56,461
Tell me about it.

685
00:42:57,931 --> 00:42:59,001
It won't happen again.

686
00:43:00,131 --> 00:43:01,301
Hey, are you okay?

687
00:43:02,271 --> 00:43:03,871
I was only thinking about you
through all this.

688
00:43:05,041 --> 00:43:06,501
I was so scared
you were going to leave me.

689
00:43:08,041 --> 00:43:09,371
My whole world went black.

690
00:43:11,041 --> 00:43:13,211
How could I ever leave you?

691
00:43:17,251 --> 00:43:18,521
Dong Suk, I just...

692
00:43:20,281 --> 00:43:22,121
I can't believe you were willing
to raise the baby.

693
00:43:23,321 --> 00:43:24,321
Why wouldn't I?

694
00:43:25,161 --> 00:43:26,961
You love my Ji Hu so much.

695
00:43:28,091 --> 00:43:29,561
So a child that's yours...

696
00:43:30,131 --> 00:43:32,161
I'm confident I could love
and raise them as my own.

697
00:43:35,731 --> 00:43:36,731
I love you.

698
00:43:39,141 --> 00:43:40,701
I really, truly love you so much,

699
00:43:41,141 --> 00:43:42,141
Dong Suk.

700
00:43:52,521 --> 00:43:54,991
- Are you ready yet?
- Yes, almost done.

701
00:43:56,591 --> 00:43:59,861
Hey, why aren't you wearing
the earrings Woo Jae got you?

702
00:44:00,221 --> 00:44:02,231
I'm the one who picked them out.
Don't you like them?

703
00:44:02,391 --> 00:44:05,261
No, it's not that.

704
00:44:05,661 --> 00:44:09,601
Have you not been talking to Woo Jae
because you're worried about me?

705
00:44:32,261 --> 00:44:33,291
It's been a while.

706
00:44:39,461 --> 00:44:42,771
So are you finally going to tell me
what's going on?

707
00:44:45,971 --> 00:44:47,171
You're not wearing the earrings.

708
00:44:56,151 --> 00:44:57,381
Wait, why are you giving these back?

709
00:44:58,021 --> 00:44:59,151
Don't you like them, by any chance?

710
00:44:59,851 --> 00:45:02,121
It's not that. I love them.

711
00:45:03,691 --> 00:45:04,721
Then why?

712
00:45:05,391 --> 00:45:08,091
I've decided not to do things
my family disapproves of anymore.

713
00:45:10,961 --> 00:45:11,961
Finally?

714
00:45:12,601 --> 00:45:16,401
I know. It's too late now, isn't it?
I should have listened to you.

715
00:45:19,401 --> 00:45:22,071
I'm sorry for being
such a bother all this time.

716
00:45:23,071 --> 00:45:25,711
Are you saying you're not going
to see me anymore?

717
00:45:30,811 --> 00:45:31,821
Yes.

718
00:45:33,151 --> 00:45:35,551
If I miss you,
no matter how hard I try not to,

719
00:45:35,621 --> 00:45:39,261
I'll pour all that energy
into what I want to do.

720
00:45:42,661 --> 00:45:43,661
Eun Bin.

721
00:45:43,731 --> 00:45:48,071
Thank you for always
being so kind to me.

722
00:45:55,841 --> 00:46:00,611
By the way, Min Seo is going back
to the US soon.

723
00:46:01,581 --> 00:46:05,351
You don't have to give up
on Min Seo because of me.

724
00:46:05,581 --> 00:46:08,521
Contact her before she leaves
and see where things go.

725
00:46:09,051 --> 00:46:12,461
I just want both you
and Min Seo to be happy.

726
00:46:31,781 --> 00:46:33,981
You put your trust in me
with such a generous offer,

727
00:46:34,381 --> 00:46:37,251
and I'm so sorry
I couldn't see it through.

728
00:46:38,281 --> 00:46:41,891
Please put all other worries aside
and just focus on your treatment.

729
00:46:42,651 --> 00:46:44,591
My father is unwell too,

730
00:46:44,921 --> 00:46:47,421
so I understand what
you must be going through, Doctor.

731
00:46:48,891 --> 00:46:50,761
Yes, thank you.

732
00:46:52,031 --> 00:46:54,301
I'll pray for the Chairman's
speedy recovery, too.

733
00:46:54,771 --> 00:46:57,001
In any case,
we at Taehan would like to...

734
00:46:57,401 --> 00:47:01,311
provide a private suite
for your comfort during treatment.

735
00:47:01,541 --> 00:47:05,711
No, please.
How could I possibly accept that?

736
00:47:06,111 --> 00:47:10,051
You're our brand's model, Doctor.
It's our duty to take care of you.

737
00:47:10,651 --> 00:47:12,221
Director Yang is
taking care of everything,

738
00:47:12,521 --> 00:47:16,321
not just the fashion show,
but all matters about you as well.

739
00:47:18,221 --> 00:47:20,991
I see.
I can tell that Director Yang...

740
00:47:21,431 --> 00:47:23,891
is truly doing
his absolute best for me.

741
00:47:23,991 --> 00:47:26,001
(Taehan Group)

742
00:47:27,361 --> 00:47:29,801
I just hope Ju Ah and I
can pull it off tomorrow.

743
00:47:30,171 --> 00:47:31,271
I'm worried.

744
00:47:41,041 --> 00:47:42,051
Turn around.

745
00:47:44,381 --> 00:47:47,851
All right, try this.
Now, look again.

746
00:47:48,321 --> 00:47:49,951
- Good.
- How's that?

747
00:47:50,021 --> 00:47:53,761
- That's great.
- Is everything perfectly prepared?

748
00:47:54,091 --> 00:47:57,131
The show is tomorrow.
You think I wouldn't have checked?

749
00:47:58,001 --> 00:48:01,931
You were humiliated during
that live Home Shopping show.

750
00:48:02,101 --> 00:48:05,101
Mom, seriously.
Why are you bringing that up now?

751
00:48:07,741 --> 00:48:11,141
Excessive tension impairs
the function of the frontal lobe,

752
00:48:11,311 --> 00:48:13,341
which can cloud your concentration.

753
00:48:13,341 --> 00:48:14,611
Mom, enough!

754
00:48:15,311 --> 00:48:17,351
Worry about yourself, not me.

755
00:48:17,611 --> 00:48:21,351
Fine, I get it. Do you have any idea
how much I've practiced?

756
00:48:21,421 --> 00:48:22,451
There's no way I'll make a mistake.

757
00:48:22,721 --> 00:48:24,621
You have to treat today's rehearsal
like the real thing.

758
00:48:24,721 --> 00:48:27,491
I get it, okay?
How many times do I have to hear it?

759
00:48:27,661 --> 00:48:28,831
So tiring.

760
00:48:30,431 --> 00:48:31,431
This is...

761
00:48:32,501 --> 00:48:34,161
a little something
I prepared for you.

762
00:48:38,471 --> 00:48:39,841
Is this a photo from my shoot?

763
00:48:40,301 --> 00:48:44,311
Yes. It's so you'll always remember
what a wonderful,

764
00:48:44,571 --> 00:48:45,781
admirable person you are, Doctor.

765
00:48:47,181 --> 00:48:50,181
I never imagined I'd get cancer
when this was taken.

766
00:48:51,281 --> 00:48:54,121
You have to come back looking
exactly like this. All right?

767
00:48:55,791 --> 00:48:57,691
Okay. I'll try my best.

768
00:48:59,791 --> 00:49:00,791
And one more thing.

769
00:49:02,861 --> 00:49:03,861
Here.

770
00:49:05,201 --> 00:49:07,061
These are family tickets
for the fashion show.

771
00:49:09,531 --> 00:49:11,231
(Executive Director: Gong Ju Ah)

772
00:49:12,771 --> 00:49:16,141
Tomorrow's the big day
Ju Ah finally makes her debut...

773
00:49:16,471 --> 00:49:18,311
as the fashion show's
executive director.

774
00:49:20,741 --> 00:49:21,751
It is, isn't it?

775
00:49:22,081 --> 00:49:24,611
I really hope all her hard work
pays off.

776
00:49:25,781 --> 00:49:29,591
I just hope she gets the recognition
she deserves this time.

777
00:49:31,561 --> 00:49:34,421
May I say something
that might be out of line?

778
00:49:35,531 --> 00:49:39,331
More than anyone,
Ju Ah wants your approval, Doctor.

779
00:49:39,861 --> 00:49:43,371
That's why she's especially prickly
and sensitive around you.

780
00:49:46,541 --> 00:49:47,671
I know that, of course.

781
00:49:49,771 --> 00:49:50,771
It's just...

782
00:49:51,241 --> 00:49:53,941
When Ju Ah finds out
that you're sick,

783
00:49:54,811 --> 00:49:58,681
I don't want her to look back
and regret being so hard on you.

784
00:50:00,281 --> 00:50:02,321
Please be proud of Ju Ah.

785
00:50:02,921 --> 00:50:05,391
And be there for her
when she's struggling.

786
00:50:15,701 --> 00:50:20,171
One, two, three, four, five...

787
00:50:20,971 --> 00:50:22,071
My gosh.

788
00:50:23,571 --> 00:50:25,181
Are you practicing your walk
out here?

789
00:50:25,981 --> 00:50:29,011
I'd hate to embarrass Ju Ah
by making a mistake tomorrow.

790
00:50:29,581 --> 00:50:30,581
I see.

791
00:50:31,151 --> 00:50:32,251
But, sweetie...

792
00:50:33,021 --> 00:50:35,221
Why the long face lately?

793
00:50:35,991 --> 00:50:37,691
Oh, me?

794
00:50:38,321 --> 00:50:39,421
Is something wrong?

795
00:50:41,391 --> 00:50:44,191
No counseling, no analyzing,
no diagnosing.

796
00:50:45,131 --> 00:50:47,801
Let's just talk. Sit down, okay?

797
00:50:57,111 --> 00:50:59,441
Is your part-time job
getting to you?

798
00:51:01,341 --> 00:51:04,411
Mom, why did you marry Dad?

799
00:51:05,481 --> 00:51:10,051
- Why the sudden question?
- Was it med school? Or chemistry?

800
00:51:11,051 --> 00:51:13,291
- No.
- Then what was it?

801
00:51:14,791 --> 00:51:15,991
Your dad...

802
00:51:16,761 --> 00:51:19,061
He always made me laugh.

803
00:51:21,101 --> 00:51:25,301
I was sensitive and my emotions
were all over the place,

804
00:51:25,301 --> 00:51:29,411
but no matter how I acted,
your dad was always steady.

805
00:51:31,581 --> 00:51:36,181
No matter how mean I was,
he always came running to see me.

806
00:51:37,751 --> 00:51:39,321
It didn't matter what I became.

807
00:51:39,851 --> 00:51:42,791
He was someone
who loved me just for being me.

808
00:51:45,061 --> 00:51:48,091
So it doesn't matter to me
what you become.

809
00:51:51,531 --> 00:51:53,201
That reminds me of someone.

810
00:51:54,331 --> 00:51:55,871
Is this what an epiphany feels like?

811
00:51:56,301 --> 00:51:59,071
Hey. I thought
analyzing was off-limits.

812
00:52:00,771 --> 00:52:01,841
Thanks, Mom.

813
00:52:02,111 --> 00:52:03,811
I'm so glad
I could talk to you about this.

814
00:52:04,841 --> 00:52:06,811
- I'm heading in.
- Okay.

815
00:52:21,191 --> 00:52:23,131
Please be proud of Ju Ah.

816
00:52:23,761 --> 00:52:26,161
And be there for her
when she's struggling.

817
00:52:31,501 --> 00:52:32,841
What are you doing here?

818
00:52:33,471 --> 00:52:36,911
Get some sleep. You're the lead,
you need to look your best tomorrow.

819
00:52:38,711 --> 00:52:40,911
- Gong Ju Ah.
- What now?

820
00:52:43,481 --> 00:52:44,951
When I saw you at the rehearsal,

821
00:52:46,321 --> 00:52:49,751
you seemed more like your true self
than when you studied medicine.

822
00:52:50,791 --> 00:52:52,261
You were practically glowing.

823
00:52:55,961 --> 00:52:59,601
You must have been so hurt
that I never understood, right?

824
00:53:02,501 --> 00:53:04,701
You're so passionate about this,

825
00:53:05,301 --> 00:53:08,171
and I never once gave you credit
for it.

826
00:53:08,971 --> 00:53:10,341
I only told you to quit...

827
00:53:11,071 --> 00:53:13,841
and said such hurtful things.
I'm sorry.

828
00:53:18,721 --> 00:53:20,481
You're going to do great tomorrow.

829
00:53:21,691 --> 00:53:23,421
You always have.

830
00:53:37,171 --> 00:53:38,501
Don't cry.

831
00:53:40,171 --> 00:53:41,841
I'm truly so sorry.

832
00:53:42,711 --> 00:53:44,841
Can you please forgive me?

833
00:53:57,091 --> 00:54:00,421
You said you'd practice in secret.
Looks like you got caught.

834
00:54:06,561 --> 00:54:08,201
What's with your face?

835
00:54:08,871 --> 00:54:10,171
Did you and Ju Ah get into a fight?

836
00:54:13,371 --> 00:54:14,841
Mother...

837
00:54:16,011 --> 00:54:20,311
I guess I thought my only value was
in being Dr. Han Seong Mi.

838
00:54:21,511 --> 00:54:24,781
But my kids don't need
Dr. Han Seong Mi.

839
00:54:25,621 --> 00:54:26,851
They just need their mom.

840
00:54:28,851 --> 00:54:30,751
Do you love me
because I'm a pharmacist?

841
00:54:31,661 --> 00:54:32,661
Of course not.

842
00:54:33,321 --> 00:54:37,131
Your very presence
gives me strength and comfort.

843
00:54:37,591 --> 00:54:40,031
Exactly. That's it.

844
00:54:40,361 --> 00:54:42,101
That's what your family wants
from you.

845
00:54:44,171 --> 00:54:45,271
You're right.

846
00:54:47,071 --> 00:54:48,441
Go take a look in the yard.

847
00:54:49,911 --> 00:54:50,911
The yard?

848
00:54:54,981 --> 00:54:57,081
Hey, Dae Han! Are you all set?

849
00:55:01,221 --> 00:55:02,921
Hey, Seong Mi is coming out.

850
00:55:10,331 --> 00:55:11,731
What is all this?

851
00:55:12,031 --> 00:55:14,401
To the one who took
Korean TV shows by storm...

852
00:55:14,831 --> 00:55:17,031
and has briefly returned home,

853
00:55:17,401 --> 00:55:21,601
this is a little something
for our Han Seong Mi!

854
00:55:21,671 --> 00:55:23,341
Ta-da!

855
00:55:36,591 --> 00:55:39,591
Honey, welcome home.

856
00:55:44,761 --> 00:55:46,331
Dae Han!

857
00:55:51,201 --> 00:55:52,201
Oh, my.

858
00:55:54,571 --> 00:55:57,211
- This brings back memories.
- Doesn't it?

859
00:55:57,941 --> 00:55:59,941
Honey, here, have a seat.

860
00:56:02,551 --> 00:56:05,081
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

861
00:56:07,551 --> 00:56:11,691
I was racking my brain to figure out
what to do, even looking online.

862
00:56:12,091 --> 00:56:16,491
Then I remembered how much you loved
stargazing by the Han River.

863
00:56:18,231 --> 00:56:19,301
I sure did.

864
00:56:20,661 --> 00:56:24,031
We'd pitch that little tent
by the Han River...

865
00:56:24,601 --> 00:56:28,571
and talk about how our life would be
after Ju Ah was born. Remember that?

866
00:56:29,511 --> 00:56:30,711
Of course, I remember.

867
00:56:32,381 --> 00:56:35,451
We said we wouldn't get greedy
trying to get ahead of others.

868
00:56:35,951 --> 00:56:38,721
And we'd just laugh and be happy.
That's what we said.

869
00:56:39,681 --> 00:56:40,681
That's right.

870
00:56:41,651 --> 00:56:43,151
But I'm sorry.

871
00:56:44,091 --> 00:56:46,661
After promising I'd make you laugh
all the time...

872
00:56:48,021 --> 00:56:49,461
It's not too late.

873
00:56:49,791 --> 00:56:50,791
Right.

874
00:56:51,491 --> 00:56:55,201
I know you'll have to put being
Dr. Han Seong Mi on hold for a bit,

875
00:56:55,401 --> 00:56:57,071
but please don't feel too lost.

876
00:56:57,401 --> 00:56:59,641
I'll make sure you have plenty
to laugh about from now on.

877
00:57:00,541 --> 00:57:04,341
Honey, I even brought you
a little monkey.

878
00:57:04,441 --> 00:57:05,441
Just a second.

879
00:57:10,711 --> 00:57:13,251
- You're ridiculous.
- A spitting image, right?

880
00:57:13,581 --> 00:57:14,581
You're unbelievable.

881
00:57:22,431 --> 00:57:25,631
Yes.
Being sick isn't so bad after all.

882
00:57:34,671 --> 00:57:36,071
So many stars out tonight.

883
00:57:37,211 --> 00:57:38,211
There really are.

884
00:57:47,021 --> 00:57:48,121
My Se Ri, today...

885
00:57:49,291 --> 00:57:51,991
Wait, what's this?

886
00:57:53,061 --> 00:57:56,331
It's the store operations manual.
I brought it home to study.

887
00:57:56,931 --> 00:58:00,601
Wow, Se Ri. You're working so hard.

888
00:58:01,931 --> 00:58:03,331
So, honey.

889
00:58:04,331 --> 00:58:06,441
What are we going to do
about Hyun Bin?

890
00:58:06,801 --> 00:58:08,841
We can't just let him leave
like this.

891
00:58:09,841 --> 00:58:12,611
Maybe I should have him over
this weekend so we can talk.

892
00:58:13,081 --> 00:58:14,681
Could you give him a call?

893
00:58:15,141 --> 00:58:16,711
Sure, I'll do that.

894
00:58:17,181 --> 00:58:18,251
You should get to work.

895
00:58:18,551 --> 00:58:20,781
Aren't you coming?
I'll give you a ride to the store.

896
00:58:21,121 --> 00:58:23,651
The store is all set up now,
so I don't need to go in so early.

897
00:58:23,891 --> 00:58:26,891
I thought I'd pack lunches
for you and your father today.

898
00:58:26,961 --> 00:58:30,761
- You don't have to do that.
- But I want to.

899
00:58:32,001 --> 00:58:33,001
Go on, get going.

900
00:58:33,101 --> 00:58:34,331
Here, Father.

901
00:58:36,101 --> 00:58:37,401
I told you
we could just get delivery.

902
00:58:37,771 --> 00:58:41,201
Father, please,
just let me do this. I want to.

903
00:58:41,601 --> 00:58:43,211
All right, thank you for the food.

904
00:58:44,771 --> 00:58:48,981
He was busy with patients and left.
Please enjoy your meal, Father.

905
00:58:58,151 --> 00:59:00,421
- Remember your treatments.
- Thank you.

906
00:59:00,491 --> 00:59:01,931
Okay, take care now.

907
00:59:01,991 --> 00:59:04,161
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

908
00:59:05,031 --> 00:59:07,231
- Dong Ik.
- Father.

909
00:59:07,831 --> 00:59:09,171
Are you having lunch already?

910
00:59:09,271 --> 00:59:11,601
No, it's not that.
Se Ri left this behind.

911
00:59:12,301 --> 00:59:14,571
She's so forgetful.

912
00:59:14,841 --> 00:59:17,571
- I'll run it over to her right now.
- Okay.

913
00:59:30,521 --> 00:59:34,691
<i>The one who left her love behind</i>

914
00:59:52,241 --> 00:59:53,241
Darn...

915
00:59:55,681 --> 00:59:58,681
(Park Soo Bin, Han Seong Mi,
Kwon Ryun Han)

916
00:59:59,021 --> 01:00:01,251
One moment. Let me check.

917
01:00:02,921 --> 01:00:05,251
- Is the waist okay?
- How's the sizing?

918
01:00:05,321 --> 01:00:06,661
Yes, I think it's fine.

919
01:00:08,591 --> 01:00:09,891
Let me check the collar.

920
01:00:11,161 --> 01:00:15,161
Look six was moved up for lighting,
so don't get mixed up.

921
01:00:15,261 --> 01:00:16,401
Right, got it.

922
01:00:16,531 --> 01:00:19,101
You know we changed look eight
to include a hat, right?

923
01:00:19,101 --> 01:00:22,611
Yes, I got the memo.
We'll give her a side ponytail.

924
01:00:22,671 --> 01:00:23,741
Okay.

925
01:00:35,591 --> 01:00:39,191
Dr. Han is also in the finale,
so make sure her hair is secure.

926
01:00:45,031 --> 01:00:46,601
You must be nervous.

927
01:00:47,761 --> 01:00:48,771
A little.

928
01:00:49,131 --> 01:00:53,741
- Relax. Just do as we rehearsed.
- Okay.

929
01:00:54,101 --> 01:00:57,111
- Let me hold your phone for you.
- Okay.

930
01:01:18,491 --> 01:01:22,501
- I'm sure it'll be spectacular.
- Yes. Oh, Director Baek is here.

931
01:01:29,311 --> 01:01:30,311
Excuse me.

932
01:01:34,981 --> 01:01:35,981
Director Baek.

933
01:01:37,251 --> 01:01:38,751
Director Yang, congratulations.

934
01:01:39,821 --> 01:01:42,451
I see you've come to witness my end.

935
01:01:42,891 --> 01:01:45,151
Well, I had to come say my goodbyes,
didn't I?

936
01:01:46,221 --> 01:01:50,191
From now on, the Fashion Division
is in your hands.

937
01:01:53,401 --> 01:01:55,261
That's a tall order,
don't you think?

938
01:02:11,781 --> 01:02:13,951
- Hello.
- Hello, there.

939
01:02:13,951 --> 01:02:16,651
It's been a while.
Let me show you to your seats.

940
01:02:16,721 --> 01:02:18,721
Yes, let's go. This way.

941
01:02:30,201 --> 01:02:33,601
You must be Gong Ju Ah,
the head of the fashion show.

942
01:02:35,571 --> 01:02:37,141
Hello, Director Baek.

943
01:02:37,911 --> 01:02:42,151
Director Yang's career is at stake,
so I'll be expecting a good outcome.

944
01:02:42,451 --> 01:02:45,351
Yes. I'll do my best
to ensure a successful outcome,

945
01:02:45,411 --> 01:02:48,381
so Director Yang
won't have to step down.

946
01:02:49,751 --> 01:02:51,991
Oh, boy.

947
01:02:52,691 --> 01:02:54,921
I take it you haven't heard.

948
01:03:00,661 --> 01:03:02,901
Regardless of
the fashion show's outcome,

949
01:03:03,171 --> 01:03:06,641
- he's quitting? What's going on?
- Well, about that...

950
01:03:07,841 --> 01:03:10,111
The budget was secured
on one condition...

951
01:03:10,911 --> 01:03:12,581
that Director Yang would resign.

952
01:03:16,481 --> 01:03:17,581
Hey, Gong Ju Ah.

953
01:03:18,251 --> 01:03:21,981
Director Baek is playing mind games
to sabotage the fashion show...

954
01:03:22,151 --> 01:03:24,891
and swallow not just Director Yang,
but the entire Fashion Division.

955
01:03:24,991 --> 01:03:26,521
Don't fall
for Director Baek's games.

956
01:03:26,821 --> 01:03:28,121
But why on earth...

957
01:03:28,891 --> 01:03:30,861
did Director Yang
make that decision?

958
01:03:33,731 --> 01:03:34,961
For you.

959
01:03:35,631 --> 01:03:38,001
He wanted to protect your dream,
no matter what.

960
01:03:38,771 --> 01:03:41,771
And for the sake of
our Fashion Division.

961
01:03:46,541 --> 01:03:49,951
Ms. Gong, we're on in 20 minutes.
We have to go.

962
01:03:51,381 --> 01:03:55,591
Hey, don't let this shake you.
Don't let his sacrifice be in vain.

963
01:03:55,651 --> 01:03:57,821
Give it your all and kill it.
Got it?

964
01:04:12,201 --> 01:04:14,541
All right, Mr. Park,
have you distributed all the lists?

965
01:04:14,801 --> 01:04:16,511
- Everyone, did you all get one?
- Yes.

966
01:04:16,511 --> 01:04:18,571
Okay, no nerves.
You got this! All right?

967
01:04:18,641 --> 01:04:19,741
We got this!

968
01:04:19,741 --> 01:04:22,281
Okay, you're all the best,
so don't worry. Don't you worry.

969
01:04:22,611 --> 01:04:23,611
Here we go.

970
01:04:24,851 --> 01:04:25,951
Focus, everyone.

971
01:04:30,551 --> 01:04:32,421
Yes, this is
Dr. Han Seong Mi's phone.

972
01:04:32,791 --> 01:04:34,361
Is this Ms. Han Seong Mi's phone?

973
01:04:34,861 --> 01:04:37,961
Yes, who's calling?
I'm her daughter. You can tell me.

974
01:04:38,131 --> 01:04:39,861
You're her daughter.

975
01:04:39,861 --> 01:04:41,731
This is
Myungjin University Hospital.

976
01:04:42,061 --> 01:04:46,141
We're calling about
her breast cancer surgery.

977
01:05:44,831 --> 01:05:47,531
(Recipe For Love)

978
01:05:47,601 --> 01:05:52,071
Should you be up and about?
I heard you have breast cancer.

979
01:05:54,601 --> 01:05:59,041
She can't suspect. Just find out
what's between her and that man.

980
01:05:59,041 --> 01:06:00,581
What's your English name?

981
01:06:00,581 --> 01:06:02,581
- Veronica.
- What's with the seaweed soup?

982
01:06:02,581 --> 01:06:04,251
Is it someone's birthday today?

983
01:06:05,051 --> 01:06:09,591
- Are you really not scared?
- Of course not. I'm off.

984
01:06:10,539 --> 01:06:12,439
Dramaday.me
